	   <tr><td colspan=2>Dear 58 Evoker, <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;  Sorry to hear about your misconceptions,<br>limitations, and discriminations. I am a level<br>49 wizard, work well in groups when I need to<br>(planes, Necropolis) and have got less than<br>5% of my xp from groups, i.e. 95% soloing.<br>Agility isn't for tanking; no one ever said <br>anything about hitting the mobs. It is for <br>casting and escaping when things go wrong, <br>which happens no matter how good you are, <br>particularly where the loot and xp is good.<br>The truth is you can learn to solo any class<br>if you are a good player, and that does not<br>hurt how you play in groups. You also might <br>try a little more tolerance of people who don't <br>play the way you do.    Alondin Octagorn<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
